<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,802,1127]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,263,839,865]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<typeStatus box="[196,256,839,865]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Type</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
In Faust’s collection at 
<collectionCode box="[558,644,840,866]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">SMTD</collectionCode>
, is a male mounted on a card (right fore tarsus beyond segment 
<number box="[1421,1436,840,866]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2.0">2</number>
missing) bearing the handwritten labels: “Chanskaja, Plüschtsch. [Chanskaja Stavka (Plüschtschevsky- Plüschtschik)]” “[golden square]”, and fitting the 
<typeStatus box="[772,825,914,940]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">type</typeStatus>
locality as “Chanskaja Stavka (Plüschtschevsky- Plüschtschik)”. It is here designated as 
<typeStatus box="[612,719,952,978]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">lectotype</typeStatus>
and has been labeled “ 
<typeStatus box="[989,1125,952,978]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Lectotypus</typeStatus>
, 
<number box="[1137,1159,951,977]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="3.0">3</number>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Faust, Gultekin" authorityName="Faust, Gultekin" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subulatus">
<emphasis box="[1174,1357,952,977]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Lixus subulatus</emphasis>
Faust, Gültekin
</taxonomicName>
des. 
<number box="[331,397,989,1015]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2008.0">2008</number>
” (
<figureCitation box="[426,521,989,1015]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12. 8" captionStartId="8.[151,276,1968,1992]" captionTargetBox="[163,1429,215,1935]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,197,1945]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. 8. Lixus lecontei Faust (Lectotypus), 9. Lixus professus Faust (Lectotypus), 10. Lixus kraatzi Capiomont (from Iġdır), 11. Lixus subulatus Faust (Lectotypus), 12. Lixus pallipes Zumpt (Lectotypus)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/294297/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Fig. 
<number box="[487,521,989,1015]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
). Three females mounted on cards with the same labels above, are here designated as 
<typeStatus box="[315,484,1026,1052]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">paralectotypes</typeStatus>
with “ 
<typeStatus box="[561,740,1026,1052]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Paralectotypus</typeStatus>
, Ƥ/Ƥ/Ƥ, 
<taxonomicName authority="Faust, Gultekin" authorityName="Faust, Gultekin" box="[849,1220,1026,1052]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subulatus">
<emphasis box="[849,1032,1026,1051]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Lixus subulatus</emphasis>
Faust, Gültekin
</taxonomicName>
des. 
<number box="[1282,1344,1026,1052]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2008.0">2008</number>
. One of the 
<typeStatus box="[194,363,1064,1090]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">paralectotypes</typeStatus>
has no right funicle, another has no right fore tarsus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
